\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 36. T. alpestre} Sibth. & Sm., {\i loc. cit.} (1809). Dwarf, densely branched, hairy shrub up to 20 cm. Stem with patent hairs. Leaves 4-10 mm, obovate to linear, with 3-5 crenations, flat or with revolute margins, cuneate at the base, subsessile. Flowers in a terminal head, with occasional solitary, axillary flowers. Calyx campanulate, evenly hairy with dense short hairs; veins obscure. Corolla creamy yellow; proximal lobes spathulate. •{\i  Kriti and Karpathos.} Cr.
\par

