\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 39. T. cossonii} D. Wood,{\i  Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  65}: 261 (1972) ({\i T. pulverulentum} (Barc.) Rouy, non (Jordan & Fourr.) F. W. Schultz & F. Winter). Dwarf shrub up to 30 cm. Stock very woody. Stem and leaves evenly covered with branched hairs. Leaves 15-30 mm, narrowly oblanceolate, slightly revolute, entire or shallowly crenate, subsessile. Flowers in terminal and lateral heads. Bracts leaf-like, the lower longer than, the upper equalling the calyx. Calyx 5-6 mm, evenly hairy. Corolla red; proximal lobes short, triangular.{\i  Calcareous rocks. • Mallorca.} Bl.
\par

