\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 40. T. libanitis} Schreber, {\i Pl. Vert. Unilab.} 48 (1773) ({\i T. verticillatum} Cav.). Dwarf shrub. Stems 15-25 cm, densely hairy. Leaves 10-15 mm, linear, entire, very densely hairy beneath, sessile, in whorls of 4; margins revolute. Flowers in a terminal subconical head. Bracts entire, spathulate. Calyx 4-5 mm; teeth very short, obtuse. Corolla yellowish; proximal lateral lobes triangular.{\i  Dry hill sides ; calcicole. • S.E. Spain.} Hs.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 41. T. carthaginense} Lange, {\i Vid. Meddel. Dansk Naturh. Foren. Kjøbenhavn}{\b  1881}: 97 (1882). Dwarf shrub. Stems 15-25 cm, hairy. Leaves 10-13 mm, spathulate, with 3-5 crenations, in small fascicles; margins revolute. Flowers in a terminal subcylindrical to globose head. Bracts entire, linear-lanceolate. Calyx 6-8 mm, strongly ribbed. Corolla white; proximal lobes narrowly triangular. {\i Rocky hillsides; calcicole. •  S.E. Spain.} Hs.
\par

