\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 42. T. aragonense} Loscos & Pardo, {\i Ser. Pl. Arag. }85 (1863). Dwarf shrub. Stems 10-40 cm, hairy; flowering stems slender, straight. Leaves 15-20 mm, linear to spathulate, entire, green above, white-hairy beneath, sessile. Flowers in a simple or compound terminal head. Bracts leaf-like. Calyx 4-5 mm, subglabrous, with sericeous teeth. Corolla white or purple; proximal lobes triangular. •{\i  E. Spain.} Hs.
\par

